                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3673.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul-General at
                            Monterey</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate-General</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>.<lb/>[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1912-04-21T22:40:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1912-04-20T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>] (Received April
                        21, 1912—10.40 p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Much talk about American intervention, which has been twice declared foolish by
                    our Government. There are strong reasons why there ought not to be any military
                    intervention and not one in favor of it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
